<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="184" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1490,1590]" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1490,1517]" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">Distribution.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[483,621,1491,1517]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Minagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caldense">
<emphasis box="[483,621,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">M. caldense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Santos" authorityYear="1967" box="[637,808,1492,1517]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Minagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canaanense">
<emphasis box="[637,808,1492,1517]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">M. canaanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a limited range of occurrence and to this date it is known only from the States of 
<collectingRegion box="[505,666,1527,1553]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[722,878,1527,1553]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="8" pageNumber="184">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
. It is also a rare species in collections, and of the examined material the most recent specimen was collected in 1988.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
